If the guards did not see his face when he turned into a bed at night, he said he was awakened and forced to turn on his back.
Counsel Manning filed a formal objection to Manning's ill-treatment in January 2011.
In April 2011, Manning was transferred to a military prison in Fort Livenworth, Kansas.
Furthermore, on Friday, the judge questioned Manning about the statement he made during Thursday ' s testimony that after he was forced to sleep naked in his cell at Quantico, he was forced to stand naked in front of guards and other prisoners for the morning ' s inspection.
